## 📖 Concepts Solidified on Retake

- **Software Release Cycles** — stability-focused releases (RHEL, Debian) 
  vs. fast-moving releases (Fedora, openSUSE Tumbleweed) — different 
  priorities for enterprises vs. developers
- **Linux vs. UNIX Architecture** — how Linux relates to the broader 
  UNIX family, including where macOS fits into that lineage
- **Backward Compatibility** — how older software continues to run on 
  newer systems
- **Embedded Systems & IoT** — Linux isn't limited to servers — it also 
  runs on embedded devices, smart TVs, and IoT hardware

